#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/rakshasa.md:22
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Skills** Deception +10, Insight +8    \n"
"**Damage Vulnerabilities.** piercing from magic weapons wielded by good "
"creatures    \n"
"**Damage Immunities** bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing from nonmagical "
"attacks    \n"
"**Senses** darkvision 60 ft., passive Perception 13    \n"
"**Languages** Common, Infernal    \n"
"**Challenge** 13 (10,000 XP) \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/rakshasa.md:28
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Limited Magic Immunity.** The rakshasa can't be affected or detected by "
"spells of 6th level or lower unless it wishes to be. It has advantage on "
"saving throws against all other spells and magical effects.     \n"
"**Innate Spellcasting.** The rakshasa's innate spellcasting ability is "
"Charisma (spell save DC 18, +10 to hit with spell attacks). The rakshasa can "
"innately cast the following spells, requiring no material components:    \n"
"At will: **_detect thoughts, disguise self, mage hand, minor illusion_**    "
"\n"
"3/day each: **_charm person, detect magic, invisibility, major image, "
"suggestion_**    \n"
"1/day each: **_dominate person, fly, plane shift, true seeing_** \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/monsters/rakshasa.md:31
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"### Actions \n"
"**Multiattack.** The rakshasa makes two claw attacks.    \n"
"**Claw.** _Melee Weapon Attack:_ +7 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. _Hit:_ "
"9 (2d6 + 2) slashing damage, and the target is cursed if it is a "
"creature. The magical curse takes effect whenever the target takes a short "
"or long rest, filling the target's thoughts with horrible images and "
"dreams. The cursed target gains no benefit from finishing a short or long "
"rest. The curse lasts until it is lifted by a remove curse spell or similar "
"magic.\n"
msgstr ""
